"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-news-2024-8-12-paris-2024-olympics-close-los-angeles-takes-torch-five-key-takeaways\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As the 2024 games end with a spectacular closing ceremony, we take a look back on the two-week sports spectacular.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 114, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  The Paris Olympics 2024has come to an endwith a spectacular closing ceremony in the Stade de Francecelebratingthe athletes and their feats over the two-week event.\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony also offered a glimpse of what could be in store in 2028 when Los Angeles will play host.\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 369, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.932132942933396e-15, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are five key takeaways from this year's Olympics:  Paris brought down the curtain on anOlympic Gamesthat brought scintillating sport to the heart of the French capital, breathing new life into an Olympic brand hurt by the difficulties of Rio de Janeiro's 2016 Games and Tokyo's COVID-hit event.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.128912607271945e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9472994043163447, \"rank\": 0.03512348437722648, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.817638646854383e-22, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9959478086854177, \"rank\": 0.004068678363497334, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even\\u00a0Parisians were carried away by the Olympic fervour.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We wanted to dream.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We got Leon Marchand,\\\" Paris 2024 chief Tony Estanguet told the crowd, referring to the French swimmer who took home four golds and won a legion of new fans.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9994425577284992, \"rank\": 0.000550886797806947, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 801, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.949641843906999e-32, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 866, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9472994043163447, \"rank\": 0.03512348437722648, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Together, we lived the games as never seen before, a whale even took part in the the surfing finals in Haiti.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999697477138826, \"rank\": 3.0147497333956662e-05, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From one day to the next, time stopped and a whole country vibrated,\\\" Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France rediscovered itself.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1136, \"end\": 1142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999642630638169, \"rank\": 3.0817031501072346e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From one day to the next, the whole of France became Olympic,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999642630638169, \"rank\": 3.0817031501072346e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also mentioned that the Olympic Games saw \\\"the most marriage proposals ever\\\".\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"COVID-19 forced Tokyo to delay the Olympics by a year until 2021 and then stage a much restricted event.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1320, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999991020408227, \"rank\": 8.926560930465976e-07, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}, {\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9959478086854177, \"rank\": 0.004068678363497334, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris promised \\\"light at the end of the tunnel\\\" and a more carefree games.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.128912607271945e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Russia's war in Ukraine on Europe's eastern flank, Israel's war on Gaza, and France's heightened state of alert over security loomed large as the games finally got under way.\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9996943065046576, \"rank\": 0.00027241003708728626, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, 