dia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You showed us what greatness human beings are capable of,\\\" Bach said as he took to the stage.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0945837636919265e-13, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You lived together, you embraced each other even though some countries are divided and at war.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You lived in peace.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thank you for making us believe in a better world for everyone.\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know that the Olympic Games cannot create peace but the Olympic Games can create a culture of peace that inspires the world.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is why I call on everyone who shares this Olympic spirit: Let us live this culture of peace every single day.\\\"\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the City of Light to the City of Angels and Hollywood.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999993224264, \"rank\": 6.77376025919832e-10, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Paris wound up its games, the Olympic flag was officially handed over to Los Angeles, which will host the 2028 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2386, \"end\": 2391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.128912607271945e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.932132942933396e-15, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LA Mayor Karen Bass gave the Olympic flag to US gymnast Simone Biles to hold as H E R sang the US national anthem live at the Stade de France, crammed with more than 70,000 people.\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2517, \"end\": 2527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}, {\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.5195119290373904, \"rank\": 0.6164279508860282, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 2603, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\"